  "20 m/s — the velocity equals the final position value of 20 m read directly from the y-axis of the graph, since position and velocity are interchangeable": "",
  "5 m/s — the velocity equals the time value of 5 seconds read from the x-axis of the graph, because time and velocity share the same numerical value": "",
  "Velocity = slope of the x-t graph = Δx/Δt = 20 m / 5 s = 4 m/s. The constant slope indicates uniform velocity.": "",
